 Trebuchets outside the enemy's town and giving the engineers the order to fire at will..../em shudder<br>
<br>
DAoC looks like EQ2 with no choice between PvP or non-PvP and slightly better graphics.<br>
<br>
Dawn looks cool on paper, but I think it's vaporware.<br>
<br>
UO is stuck in the age of 2D<br>
<br>
UO2 was cancelled, that's when I decided to follow SB<br>
<br>
Neocron looks like it may be pretty cool, if you're into guns and Sci-Fi style settings.  I may try this one if I can test it out in Beta.<br>
<br>
Jumpgate, I got into the Beta, and I have summed my experience up into one word, booooooring.  The actual game mechanics behind your spaceship is sooo neanderthal, there isn't even damage locations or anything.  I was hoping for something more along the lines of the Wing Commander games I've played, and was nothing short of totally disappointed.<br>
<br>
That's about the only ones that have even caught my eye as far as MMORPGs go.  If you're into Tactical/Strategy style sims, try out MechCommander 2, but make sure you have a good Vid Card.  I've been playing it the past few days, it's sooo hard to pull myself away from the storyline to play EQ.  I've always been into the Battletech based games, ever since FASA put it on paper, though.<br>
